author: Russell Brand
description:
74-year-old activist Audrey White has been violently arrested under UK terrorism laws for holding a pro-Palestine sign, sparking outrage over free speech and state overreach. Once praised for confronting Keir Starmer face-to-face, White now faces house arrest as Britain accelerates toward authoritarianism. From mass protests and arrests to the criminalization of dissent, this moment exposes a broken political contract between the government and its people.
